node.text:
The COVID-19 pandemic has cost schoolchildren 1.8 trillion hours ‒ and counting ‒ of in-class learning. This cannot go on.

Futures are at stake. Our message to world leaders is clear: #ReopenSchools as soon as possible. The clock is ticking.

#UNGA

"I'm going back to school. I'm so happy. I've been waiting a year and a half. Education is very important and we can learn better at school," says 10-year-old Amanda from Chile.

We must get students back in classrooms as soon as possible. 

#ReopenSchools

node.text:
Lyuba's school was bombed beyond recognition in eastern Ukraine. This is what it looks like now.

Hostilities across the world have devastated young people's access to education, and COVID-19 has made things even worse.

Whether living through peace or conflict, children's right to learn must be protected. 

#NotATarget

#UNGA

We’ll be back tomorrow. When will they be back in school?
